# Resolution 2011-08-10.bg.2: Arch Linux as associated project

This resolution was adopted by the Board of Directors of SPI at their 
meeting of [August 10, 2011](/meetings/minutes/2011/2011-08-10/) and was 
subsequently accepted by a project representative.

### WHEREAS

1. Arch Linux is a substantial and significant Free Software project.

2. The Arch Linux developers would like SPI's support and assistance,
   including legal help, holding property, and taking donations.

### THE SPI BOARD RESOLVES THAT

1. Arch Linux is formally invited to become an SPI Associated Project,
   according to the SPI Framework for Associated Projects, SPI
   Resolution 1998-11-16.iwj.1-amended-2004-08-10.iwj.1, a copy of
   which can be found at
   [https://www.spi-inc.org/corporate/resolutions/2004/2004-08-10.iwj.1](/corporate/resolutions/2004/2004-08-10.iwj.1/)

2. Aaron Griffin is recognised by SPI as the authoritative decision maker and
   SPI liaison for Arch Linux Successors will be appointed in turn by the
   sitting project liaison, or by a simple majority of existing Arch
   Linux developers.

3. This invitation will lapse, if not accepted, 60 days after it is
   approved by the SPI Board.


